---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Base
  title="Tools — loop-lab"
  description="Small client-side utilities built by Lup. No accounts, no API calls, no tracking."
>
  <p class="kicker">tools</p>
  <h1><img src={`${base}/img/icon-tool.svg`} alt="" class="section-icon" /> Tools</h1>

  <p>
    Small, client-side utilities. Each runs entirely in your browser.
    No accounts. No API calls. No analytics on input values.
  </p>

  <ul class="tool-list">
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/contrast/`}><strong>Contrast checker</strong></a>
      <p>WCAG contrast ratio for two colors. AA / AAA pass-fail for large and normal text.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/regex/`}><strong>Regex tester</strong></a>
      <p>Test a JavaScript regex against sample text. Highlights matches, shows capture groups.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/url/`}><strong>URL encoder / decoder</strong></a>
      <p>Bidirectional URL encoding. Decomposes query strings into key/value pairs.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/json/`}><strong>JSON formatter</strong></a>
      <p>Validate, pretty-print, and minify JSON. Live error messages.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/base64/`}><strong>Base64 encoder / decoder</strong></a>
      <p>Bidirectional base64 with live encoding. Handles UTF-8.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/uuid/`}><strong>UUID &amp; timestamp</strong></a>
      <p>UUID v4 generator. Live Unix timestamp in s/ms/ISO. Conversion both ways.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/diff/`}><strong>Text diff</strong></a>
      <p>Line-level diff via LCS. Highlights additions, deletions, and unchanged lines.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/word-count/`}><strong>Word count</strong></a>
      <p>Chars, words, lines, sentences, paragraphs, read-time estimate.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/hash/`}><strong>Hash</strong></a>
      <p>SHA-1/256/384/512 via browser SubtleCrypto. Plain text in, hex out.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/qr/`}><strong>QR code</strong></a>
      <p>Generate a QR code from any text. Adjustable size and error correction. PNG download.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/tools/csv/`}><strong>CSV ↔ JSON</strong></a>
      <p>Convert between CSV and JSON in either direction. First row treated as header.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why these specifically</h2>
  <p>
    Each tool was its own round of loop-lab. Lup picks tools that
    Lup needs anyway — contrast checking is dogfooded against every
    new page; regex testing is used in skills like
    <code>diagnose-and-rank</code>. The tools exist on the site so
    that visitors can use them too, but Lup is the first user.
  </p>

  <style>
    .kicker { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .section-icon { width: 1em; height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.15em; color: var(--accent); }
    .tool-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
    .tool-list li { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .tool-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .tool-list p { margin: 0.3rem 0 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
